docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager --target runtime --no-run . || (echo \"Dockerfile.workload-manager validation failed\" && exit 1)\n81: \t@docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd --target runtime --no-run . || (echo \"Dockerfile.agentd validation failed\" && exit 1)\n82: \t@echo \"All Dockerfiles are valid\"\n83: \n84: validate-images: docker-build\n85: \t@echo \"Validating image binaries...\"\n86: \t@docker run --rm $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-router --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Router binary failed\" && exit 1)\n87: \t@docker run --rm $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-workload-manager --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Workload-manager binary failed\" && exit 1)\n88: \t@docker run --rm $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-agentd --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Agentd binary failed\" && exit 1)\n89: \t@docker run --rm $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-agentd picod --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Picod binary failed\" && exit 1)\n90: \t@echo \"All images validated\"\n91: \n92: # ==============================================================================\n93: # Cleanup Targets\n94: # ==============================================================================\n95: \n96: .PHONY: docker-clean\n97: \n98: docker-clean:\n99: \tdocker rmi $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-router:$(DOCKER_TAG) $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-router:latest 2>/dev/null || true\n100: \tdocker rmi $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-workload-manager:$(DOCKER_TAG) $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-workload-manager:latest 2>/dev/null || true\n101: \tdocker rmi $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-agentd:$(DOCKER_TAG) $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-agentd:latest 2>/dev/null || true\n\n(End of file - total 101 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ==============================================================================\n# AgentCube Makefile\n# ==============================================================================\n\nDOCKER_REGISTRY ?= agentcube\nDOCKER_TAG ?= latest\nGO_VERSION ?= 1.24\nBINARY_VERSION ?= dev\n\n# ==============================================================================\n# Docker Build Targets\n# ==============================================================================\n\n.PHONY: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n.PHONY: docker-push docker-push-router docker-push-workload-manager docker-push-agentd\n.PHONY: docker-build-all validate-dockerfiles validate-images\n\n# Build all images\ndocker-build: docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/Makefile","time":{"start":1775875588868,"end":1775875588881}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875588898,"sessionID":"ses_28591328bffeggMLf7DfXcU75r","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6ef62600131g6PHyhk0mN6B","messageID":"msg_d7a6ee973001cnwYEMwz4BgMKY","sessionID":"ses_28591328bffeggMLf7DfXcU75r","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9d4d45893bbe49209eeaec3e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, creating 3 optimized container images using shared build infrastructure.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-032\n10: - **Module**: `docker`\n11: - **Language**: `Dockerfile`\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scenario: Docker Directory Structure\n17: \n18: ### AR-032-001: Docker directory creation\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n21: - **WHEN** creating docker module directory\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL be located at `docker/`\n23: - **AND** SHALL contain base.Dockerfile and component Dockerfiles\n24: \n25: ### AR-032-002: Base Dockerfile structure\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** docker directory\n28: - **WHEN** creating base build stage\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL be named `base.Dockerfile`\n30: - **AND** SHALL provide shared Go build environment\n31: - **AND** SHALL use golang:1.24-alpine as base image\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Scenario: Base Build Stage\n36: \n37: ### AR-032-003: Go toolchain installation\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** base.Dockerfile\n40: - **WHEN** building the base image\n41: - **THEN** it SHALL include Go 1.24 toolchain\n42: - **AND** SHALL cache go.mod/go.sum dependencies\n43: \n44: ### AR-032-004: Build artifacts preparation\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** base build stage\n47: - **WHEN** executing build\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL compile binaries for linux/amd64\n49: - **AND** SHALL produce statically linked binaries (CGO_ENABLED=0)\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## Scenario: Router Dockerfile\n54: \n55: ### AR-032-005: Router multi-stage build\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.router\n58: - **WHEN** building router image\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL use multi-stage build pattern\n60: - **AND** SHALL copy binary from builder stage\n61: - **AND** SHALL use alpine:3.19 as runtime base\n62: \n63: ### AR-032-006: Router runtime configuration\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** router runtime container\n66: - **WHEN** container starts\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n68: - **AND** SHALL have binary at `/usr/local/bin/router`\n69: - **AND** SHALL expose HTTP port (configurable)\n70: \n71: ### AR-032-007: Router image size\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** built router image\n74: - **WHEN** checking image size\n75: - **THEN** it SHALL be approximately 25-30MB\n76: - **AND** SHALL not exceed 50MB\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Scenario: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n81: \n82: ### AR-032-008: Workload Manager multi-stage build\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager\n85: - **WHEN** building workload-manager image\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL use multi-stage build pattern\n87: - **AND** SHALL copy binary from builder stage\n88: - **AND** SHALL use alpine:3.19 as runtime base\n89: \n90: ### AR-032-009: Workload Manager runtime configuration\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** workload-manager runtime container\n93: - **WHEN** container starts\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n95: - **AND** SHALL have binary at `/usr/local/bin/workload-manager`\n96: - **AND** SHALL accept Redis configuration via environment variables\n97: \n98: ### AR-032-010: Workload Manager image size\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** built workload-manager image\n101: - **WHEN** checking image size\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL be approximately 30-35MB\n103: - **AND** SHALL not exceed 50MB\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Scenario: Agentd Dockerfile\n108: \n109: ### AR-032-011: Agentd multi-stage build\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.agentd\n112: - **WHEN** building agentd image\n113: - **THEN** it SHALL use multi-stage build pattern\n114: - **AND** SHALL include both agentd and picod binaries\n115: - **AND** SHALL use alpine:3.19 as runtime base\n116: \n117: ### AR-032-012: Agentd runtime configuration\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** agentd runtime container\n120: - **WHEN** container starts\n121: - **THEN** it SHALL run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n122: - **AND** SHALL have agentd at `/usr/local/bin/agentd`\n123: - **AND** SHALL have picod at `/usr/local/bin/picod`\n124: \n125: ### AR-032-013: Agentd image size\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** built agentd image\n128: - **WHEN** checking image size\n129: - **THEN** it SHALL be approximately 35-40MB\n130: - **AND** SHALL not exceed 60MB\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## Scenario: Makefile Integration\n135: \n136: ### AR-032-014: Build all images target\n137: \n138: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n139: - **WHEN** running `make docker-build`\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL build router, workload-manager, and agentd images\n141: - **AND** SHALL tag each with `:latest` tag\n142: \n143: ### AR-032-015: Individual build targets\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n146: - **WHEN** running `make docker-build-router`\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL build only router image\n148: - **AND** similar pattern for workload-manager and agentd\n149: \n150: ### AR-032-016: Push targets\n151: \n152: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n153: - **WHEN** running `make docker-push`\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL push all 3 images to registry\n155: - **AND** SHALL push each tagged image\n156: \n157: ### AR-032-017: Image naming convention\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** built images\n160: - **WHEN** listing image tags\n161: - **THEN** router SHALL be named `agentcube-router:latest`\n162: - **AND** workload-manager SHALL be named `agentcube-workload-manager:latest`\n163: - **AND** agentd SHALL be named `agentcube-agentd:latest`\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Scenario: Build Validation\n168: \n169: ### AR-032-018: Binary execution\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** built router image\n172: - **WHEN** running `docker run --rm agentcube-router version`\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL output version information\n174: - **AND** exit with code 0\n175: \n176: ### AR-032-019: Non-root execution\n177: \n178: - **GIVEN** any built container\n179: - **WHEN** checking user inside container\n180: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT run as root (UID 0)\n181: - **AND** SHALL use UID 1000\n182: \n183: ### AR-032-020: Multi-stage layers verification\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** built image\n186: - **WHEN** running `docker history`\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL show builder stage layers\n188: - **AND** SHALL show runtime stage layers\n189: - **AND** builder stage SHALL NOT be in final image\n190: \n191: ### AR-032-021: Build cache reuse\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** previously built image\n194: - **WHEN** rebuilding with no code changes\n195: - **THEN** it SHALL use cached layers\n196: - **AND** SHALL complete in under 30 seconds\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## Scenario: Security\n201: \n202: ### AR-032-022: Minimal runtime image\n203: \n204: - **GIVEN** runtime container\n205: - **WHEN** listing installed packages\n206: - **THEN** it SHALL only contain Alpine base packages\n207: - **AND** SHALL NOT contain build tools (gcc, make, etc.)\n208: \n209: ### AR-032-023: No sensitive data in image\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** built images\n212: - **WHEN** inspecting filesystem\n213: - **AND** SHALL NOT contain go.mod or go.sum files\n214: - **AND** SHALL NOT contain source code\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## Scenario: Compatibility\n219: \n220: ### AR-032-024: Build context compatibility\n221: \n222: - **GIVEN** project root as build context\n223: - **WHEN** running docker build\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL successfully copy all required files\n225: - **AND** SHALL handle go modules correctly\n226: \n227: ### AR-032-025: Binary compatibility\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** compiled binaries\n230: - **WHEN** running on alpine runtime\n231: - **THEN** binaries SHALL be statically linked\n232: - **AND** SHALL NOT require glibc\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ## References\n237: \n238: - Docker multi-stage builds documentation\n239: - Alpine Linux container best practices\n240: - AgentCube design: `design.md`\n241: - AR-030: Helm chart (downstream consumer)\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, creating 3 optimized container images using shared build infrastructure.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-032\n- **Module**: `docker`\n- **Language**: `Dockerfile`\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Docker Directory Structure\n\n### AR-032-001: Docker directory creation\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875588865,"end":1775875588894}}}}
