{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775875615075,"sessionID":"ses_28591328bffeggMLf7DfXcU75r","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f6962001DCM7VLgjBSs1MG","messageID":"msg_d7a6f5d58001g39BBWkKpCwM27","sessionID":"ses_28591328bffeggMLf7DfXcU75r","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875679882,"sessionID":"ses_28591328bffeggMLf7DfXcU75r","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6f6ba1001cBPkkkQm9A17hB","messageID":"msg_d7a6f5d58001g39BBWkKpCwM27","sessionID":"ses_28591328bffeggMLf7DfXcU75r","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_c7d0fef1e6fc44e29e464d86","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, supporting Go source compilation, Docker image building, testing, linting, and development workflows.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-033\n- **Module**: `root`\n- **Language**: `Makefile`\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Binary Build Targets\n\n### AR-033-001: Build all binaries\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root with Go source code\n- **WHEN** running `make build`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile router, workload-manager, agentd, and picod binaries\n- **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/` directory\n- **AND** SHALL use CGO_ENABLED=0 for static linking\n- **AND** SHALL inject version via ldflags (-X main.version=$(BINARY_VERSION))\n\n### AR-033-002: Build individual binary - router\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-router`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only router binary\n- **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/router`\n\n### AR-033-003: Build individual binary - workload-manager\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-workload-manager`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only workload-manager binary\n- **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/workload-manager`\n\n### AR-033-004: Build individual binary - agentd\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only agentd binary\n- **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/agentd`\n\n### AR-033-005: Build individual binary - picod\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-picod`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only picod binary\n- **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/picod`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Cross-Compilation Targets\n\n### AR-033-006: Build for Linux amd64\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-linux-amd64`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for linux/amd64\n- **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/linux-amd64/` directory\n\n### AR-033-007: Build for Linux arm64\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-linux-arm64`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for linux/arm64\n- **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/linux-arm64/` directory\n\n### AR-033-008: Build for Darwin amd64\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-darwin-amd64`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for darwin/amd64\n- **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/darwin-amd64/` directory\n\n### AR-033-009: Build for Darwin arm64\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make build-darwin-arm64`\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for darwin/arm64\n- **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/darwin-arm64/` directory\n\n### AR-033-010: Cross-build all platforms\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make cross-build`\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute all cross-compilation targets\n- **AND** SHALL produce binaries for linux-amd64, linux-arm64, darwin-amd64, darwin-arm64\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Docker Build Integration\n\n### AR-033-011: Docker build all images\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile with docker targets\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build`\n- **THEN** it SHALL build router, workload-manager, and agentd images\n- **AND** SHALL tag each with :latest tag (unchanged from AR-032)\n\n### AR-033-012: Docker build individual image - router\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build-router`\n- **THEN** it SHALL build only router image\n- **AND** SHALL tag as agentcube-router:latest\n\n### AR-033-013: Docker build individual image - workload-manager\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build-workload-manager`\n- **THEN** it SHALL build only workload-manager image\n- **AND** SHALL tag as agentcube-workload-manager:latest\n\n### AR-033-014: Docker build individual image - agentd\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-build-agentd`\n- **THEN** it SHALL build only agentd image\n- **AND** SHALL tag as agentcube-agentd:latest\n\n### AR-033-015: Docker push all images\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-push`\n- **THEN** it SHALL push all 3 images to registry\n- **AND** SHALL push both versioned and latest tags\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Testing Targets\n\n### AR-033-016: Run all tests\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project with test files\n- **WHEN** running `make test`\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute unit tests\n- **AND** SHALL use `-short` flag to skip long-running tests\n- **AND** SHALL display test results verbosely\n\n### AR-033-017: Run unit tests only\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project\n- **WHEN** running `make test-unit`\n- **THEN** it SHALL run only unit tests\n- **AND** SHALL skip integration tests\n- **AND** SHALL use `-v` for verbose output\n\n### AR-033-018: Run tests with coverage\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project\n- **WHEN** running `make test-cover`\n- **THEN** it SHALL generate coverage profile (coverage.out)\n- **AND** SHALL generate HTML coverage report (coverage.html)\n- **AND** SHALL display coverage percentage\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Code Quality Targets\n\n### AR-033-019: Run linter\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project with golangci-lint config\n- **WHEN** running `make lint`\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute golangci-lint on all packages\n- **AND** SHALL report any linting issues\n- **AND** SHALL exit with non-zero code if errors found\n\n### AR-033-020: Run linter with auto-fix\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project\n- **WHEN** running `make lint-fix`\n- **THEN** it SHALL run golangci-lint with --fix flag\n- **AND** SHALL automatically fix fixable issues\n- **AND** SHALL report any unfixable issues\n\n### AR-033-021: Format code\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project\n- **WHEN** running `make fmt`\n- **THEN** it SHALL run gofmt on all Go files\n- **AND** SHALL run goimports to fix imports\n- **AND** SHALL write changes in-place (-w flag)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Development Workflow Targets\n\n### AR-033-022: Start development environment\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project with docker-compose.dev.yml\n- **WHEN** running `make dev`\n- **THEN** it SHALL start development environment via docker-compose\n- **AND** SHALL run in detached mode\n\n### AR-033-023: Start development with Docker\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project\n- **WHEN** running `make dev-docker`\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d`\n- **AND** SHALL start all required services\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Cleanup Targets\n\n### AR-033-024: Clean build artifacts\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project with built binaries\n- **WHEN** running `make clean`\n- **THEN** it SHALL remove `bin/` directory\n- **AND** SHALL remove coverage files (coverage.out, coverage.html)\n- **AND** SHALL remove any other build artifacts\n\n### AR-033-025: Clean Docker images\n\n- **GIVEN** built Docker images\n- **WHEN** running `make docker-clean`\n- **THEN** it SHALL remove router, workload-manager, and agentd images\n- **AND** SHALL handle missing images gracefully (no error if not found)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Utility Targets\n\n### AR-033-026: Display help\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile with help target\n- **WHEN** running `make help`\n- **THEN** it SHALL display all available targets\n- **AND** SHALL show categorized help text\n- **AND** SHALL include descriptions for each target category\n\n### AR-033-027: Display version\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile with version target\n- **WHEN** running `make version`\n- **THEN** it SHALL display current build version\n- **AND** SHALL show BINARY_VERSION variable value\n\n### AR-033-028: Check dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project\n- **WHEN** running `make deps`\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify Go is installed\n- **AND** SHALL verify Docker is installed\n- **AND** SHALL verify golangci-lint is installed (optional)\n- **AND** SHALL display helpful error message if any dependency is missing\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Variable Configuration\n\n### AR-033-029: Docker registry configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running make with DOCKER_REGISTRY=<custom>\n- **THEN** it SHALL use custom registry prefix for image tags\n- **AND** default value SHALL be \"agentcube\"\n\n### AR-033-030: Docker tag configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running make with DOCKER_TAG=<version>\n- **THEN** it SHALL use custom tag for images\n- **AND** default value SHALL be \"latest\"\n\n### AR-033-031: Binary version configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running make with BINARY_VERSION=<version>\n- **THEN** it SHALL inject version into binary via ldflags\n- **AND** default value SHALL be \"dev\"\n\n### AR-033-032: Go version configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** running make with GO_VERSION=<version>\n- **THEN** it SHALL use specified Go version for Docker builds\n- **AND** default value SHALL be \"1.24\"\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Default Target\n\n### AR-033-033: Default build target\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n- **WHEN** running `make` without arguments\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make build` by default\n- **AND** SHALL compile all binaries for current platform\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Error Handling\n\n### AR-033-034: Missing Go installation\n\n- **GIVEN** environment without Go installed\n- **WHEN** running any build target\n- **THEN** it SHALL display clear error message\n- **AND** SHALL indicate Go is required\n\n### AR-033-035: Missing source code\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project missing cmd/ directories\n- **WHEN** running build target\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error from go build\n- **AND** SHALL not produce misleading error messages\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Makefile Structure\n\n### AR-033-036: Self-documenting makefile\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile\n- **WHEN** examining makefile source\n- **THEN** it SHALL be organized in logical sections with comments\n- **AND** SHALL use .PHONY declarations for all non-file targets\n- **AND** SHALL define variables at the top for easy configuration\n\n### AR-033-037: Platform-independent targets\n\n- **GIVEN** Makefile targets\n- **WHEN** running on Linux, macOS, or Windows\n- **THEN** targets SHALL execute correctly\n- **AND** SHALL avoid shell-specific commands\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- AgentCube proposal: `changes/AR-033/proposal.md`\n- Existing Makefile: `Makefile`\n- AR-032: Dockerfile multi-stage builds (downstream consumer)\n- Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n- golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n\n(End of file - total 311 lines)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875679872,"end":1775875679880}}}}
